<subSubSection pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="69.[151,1436,287,565]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,262,287,312]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Material.</emphasis>
This species was observed by our colleague Philippe Willenz (Royal Belgian Institute of Natural Sciences, Bruxelles, 
<collectingCountry box="[383,481,324,349]" name="Belgium" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Belgium</collectingCountry>
) during a survey of small forereef caves between South Water Cay and Curlew Bank, 
<quantity box="[151,252,360,384]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.15" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" unit="m" value="31.5" valueMax="39.0" valueMin="24.0">24–39 m</quantity>
, in 
<date box="[293,417,359,384]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" value="1987-04">
April 
<number box="[358,417,360,384]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" value="1987.0">1987</number>
</date>
. No specimens were collected for Museum deposit.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="69.[151,1436,287,565]" box="[199,1072,396,421]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,299,396,421]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Ecology.</emphasis>
Cryptic, in dark parts of caves and on reefs (
<bibRefCitation author="Vacelet" box="[802,960,396,421]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refString="Vacelet, J. (1980) Squelette calcaire facultative et corps de regeneration dans le genre Merlia, eponges apparentees aux chaetetides fossiles. Comptes rendu, Academie de Sciences (Paris), Series D, 290, 227 - 230." type="journal article" year="1980">
Vacelet, 
<number box="[900,960,396,420]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<quantity box="[980,1067,396,421]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" unit="m" value="22.0" valueMax="39.0" valueMin="5.0">
5– 
<specimenCount box="[1007,1067,396,421]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="generic">39 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,700,431,456]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="69.[151,1436,287,565]" box="[199,700,431,456]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,431,456]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Distribution.</emphasis>
