</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="69.[151,1436,287,565]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,468,493]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Comments.</emphasis>
Characteristic spicules (clavidiscs combined with tylostyles) found as foreign components in other sponges collected in forereef caves probably originated from this species during episodes of overgrowth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="69.[151,1436,287,565]" box="[199,1396,540,565]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
The view of synonymizing 
<taxonomicName box="[507,689,540,565]" class="Demospongiae" family="Merliidae" genus="Merlia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="deficiens">
<emphasis box="[507,689,540,565]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Merlia deficiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[753,885,541,564]" class="Demospongiae" family="Merliidae" genus="Merlia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="normani">
<emphasis box="[753,885,541,564]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">M. normani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is no longer upheld (van 
<bibRefCitation author="Soest" box="[1172,1384,540,565]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refString="van Soest, R. W. M., Boury-Esnault, N., Hooper, J. N. A., Rutzler, K., de Voogd, N. J., Alvarez de Glasby, B., Hajdu, E., Pisera, A. B., Manconi, R., Schoenberg, C., Janussen, D., Tabachnick, K. R., Klautau, M., Picton, B., Kelly, M., Vacelet, J., Dohrmann, M., Cristina Diaz, M. &amp; Cardenas, P. (2013 b) World Porifera database. Available from: http: // www. marinespecies. org / porifera (accessed 5 December 2013)" type="journal article" year="2013" yearSuffix="b">
Soest 
<emphasis box="[1239,1302,540,565]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">et al.,</emphasis>
<number box="[1309,1369,540,565]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" value="2013.0">2013</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
